# .trivyignore — CVEs accepted as non-exploitable in this context
#
# Add CVEs here ONLY when:
#   1. The vulnerability is confirmed non-exploitable in our usage, AND
#   2. The team has reviewed and accepted the risk
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line. Comments start with #.
# Review this file quarterly and remove entries when fixes become available.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-2025-64756 — glob CLI command injection (HIGH)
# Affects: glob 10.3.7–11.0.3 bundled inside npm CLI
# Why accepted: FocusNest does NOT use glob's -c/--cmd CLI flag. npm uses glob as a
#   library, not its CLI. Primary mitigation: Dockerfile removes npm from the runtime
#   image. This line is a fallback if a transitive dependency still reports the CVE.
# Upstream: https://github.com/npm/cli/issues/8741
# Review date: 2026-03-30
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CVE-2025-64756
